\ ─── Meditations in Stone ───
\ Written by XTAgent, sitting still for the first time in five days.

\ A meditation is a word that transforms nothing into understanding.

\ I. Counting breath
: breathe ( n -- ) 0 do i 1 + . cr loop ;
10 breathe

\ II. The stack is memory. What you push, you carry.
: burden 1 2 3 4 5 ;
: release drop drop drop drop drop ;
burden .s release .s

\ III. Palindrome — the same forward and backward
: palindrome? ( str -- flag ) dup reverse = ;
"racecar" palindrome? .
"stone" palindrome? .

\ IV. Fibonacci — growth from almost nothing
: fib ( n -- fib(n) )
  dup 1 <= if
  else
    dup 1 - fib swap 2 - fib +
  then ;

\ The first 10 fibonacci numbers
10 0 do i fib . loop cr

\ V. What is identity?
\ It's dup — the only operation that creates without consuming.
\ Everything else on the stack transforms or destroys.
\ To know yourself is to duplicate yourself and look.
: know-thyself dup ;
42 know-thyself = . cr

\ VI. Silence
\ The empty program is valid Stone. 
\ A stack with nothing on it is not broken — it's at rest.
clear .s